<br>
I recommend they all just pick what class sounds appealing to them. Make sure you've got a tank class and someone with heal spells and if you're gonna get higher levels, someone with slow. <br>
<br>
Some classes that are especially good (not neccessarily good in the same group, but good classes in general)<br>
<br>
Bard<br>
Enchanter<br>
Shaman<br>
Cleric<br>
<br>
For my group, I'd probably go something like:<br>
Paladin<br>
Cleric<br>
Shaman<br>
Enchanter<br>
Beastlord<br>
Magician<br>
<br>
Not a real damage heavy group, so it's probably never statistically the best, but I specifically designed it that way because in that group, the rest of the group would do less damage = I do more damage = makes me happy to see more nuke messages. I'm greedy that way.. nukes make me happy.<br>
<br>
<br>
